---
title: Crunchy Veggie and Lentil Salad with a Feta-Stuffed Pita and Creamy Dill Dressing
description: We love lentils because they are protein-rich, filling, and satisfying. But their flavor might best be described as moody or earthy, which means that they go best with a few accents to lighten and brighten them up. This recipe brings in cool cucumber, carrot, and radish, plus a squeeze of sunny lemon and a breath of fresh dill. And on the side, you’ve got a feta-stuffed pita that’s brimming with cheesy goodness.
